FBIS4-18158 "drweu062_n_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-062 Daily Report 13 Mar 1994 NORDIC COUNTRIES Finland * Son of Kim Il-song Arrives as Ambassador * Son of Kim Il-song Arrives as Ambassador 94P20561A Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 13 Mar 94 p 5 94P20561A Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT Finnish CSO [Article by Unto Hamalainen: "North Korea's Leader Sends Son as Ambassador to Finland"] [Excerpt] North Korean leader Kim Il-song's second son, Kim Pyong-il, arrived Friday [11 March] in Finland. Kim Pyong-il is his country's new ambassador in the Helsinki embassy. North Korea's embassy confirmed the envoy's arrival on Saturday. The new ambassador will submit his credentials to President Martti Ahtisaari next Friday. [passage omitted]
